Common Troubleshooting Tips
SELinux Issues
Service fails to start: Check SELinux contexts and booleans
File access denied: Verify file contexts with ls -Z
Network connections blocked: Check network-related booleans
Custom applications fail: Create or modify SELinux policies
AppArmor Issues
Application crashes: Check if profile is too restrictive
Profile won't load: Verify syntax with apparmor_parser -p
Logs not appearing: Ensure auditd service is running
Profile conflicts: Check for overlapping profile rules
General Security Framework Issues
Performance degradation: Monitor system resources and optimize policies
Application compatibility: Test thoroughly in development environments
Policy maintenance: Keep profiles updated with application changes
Documentation: Maintain clear records of all policy modifications
